        <h3><u>What are otters?</u></h3>
        <p>
          Otters are carnivorous mammals in the subfamily Lutrinae. The 13
          extant otter species are all semiaquatic, aquatic or marine, with
          diets based on fish and invertebrates. Lutrinae is a branch of the
          Mustelidae family, which also includes weasels, badgers, mink, and
          wolverines, among other animals. (Source: Wikipedia)
        </p>
        <h3><u>Where are otters found?</u></h3>
        <p>
          Otters can be found in many places acros the globe. They exist in both
          Americas, Africa, Europe, and parts of Asia (primariliy southeast
          Asia). (Source: seaworld.org)
        </p>
        <h3><u>Are otters endangered?</u></h3>
        <p>
          Many species of otter are considered at risk or endangered. This is
          mostly due to changing habitats and other climate-related isssues.
          (Source: otter-world.com)
        </p>
